cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.DB, cs.SI, cs.CE

The paper describes a data fusion approach using matrix factorization, which is a common technique in machine learning and data mining. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper also deals with the integration of heterogeneous data sets, which is a common problem in artificial intelligence and databases, making cs.AI and cs.DB likely sub-categories as well. The paper also discusses the use of contextual data and system constraints, which are relevant to social networks and complex systems, making cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) a possible sub-category. Finally, the paper applies the proposed approach to gene function prediction and pharmacologic actions, which are relevant to computational biology and bioinformatics, making cs.CE (Computational Engineering, Finance, and Science) a possible sub-category.
